  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 52-year-old woman presents to the clinic two weeks after undergoing thyroid lobectomy for a solitary thyroid nodule. She reports persistent hoarseness and occasional difficulty swallowing liquids. Examination reveals a breathy voice. Indirect laryngoscopy shows reduced movement of the left vocal fold in a paramedian position. Her gag reflex is intact, tongue strength is normal, and there are no palpable neck masses.\nWhich structure was most likely injured during surgery to account for her symptoms?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Hypoglossal nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Recurrent laryngeal nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Glossopharyngeal nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "External branch of the superior laryngeal nerve"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z28579fa063b554ba93bdf1a8ea853881\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z28579fa063b554ba93bdf1a8ea853881\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"GqaB-l\">hypoglossal nerve</a> innervates <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-section-id=\"p9cLoe0\">tongue</a> muscles, and its injury causes <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-section-id=\"p9cLoe0\">tongue</a> deviation, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z8d1de503affe568a214e9d9b436497d6\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z8d1de503affe568a214e9d9b436497d6\" data-section-id=\"69cjoe0\">mastication</a> difficulties, and slurred speech. Normal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-section-id=\"p9cLoe0\">tongue</a> strength and an intact <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Zac08e08784826ab14a9615a73789c357\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Zac08e08784826ab14a9615a73789c357\" data-section-id=\"xAXEN00\" data-sememe-id=\"hNbca8\">gag reflex</a> indicate proper <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z28579fa063b554ba93bdf1a8ea853881\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z28579fa063b554ba93bdf1a8ea853881\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"GqaB-l\">hypoglossal nerve</a> function, making it unlikely to cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"-EWDyM0\">vocal fold paralysis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">recurrent laryngeal nerve</a> is at risk during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\">thyroid surgery</a> due to its proximity to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid gland</a>. It provides motor innervation to most intrinsic laryngeal muscles, essential for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal fold</a> movement and voice production. Injury to this nerve results in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"-EWDyM0\">vocal fold paralysis</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3u0SI3&anker=Zd7f9061edc1020a411ebccbb319b47ec\" data-learningcard-id=\"3u0SI3\" data-anker=\"Zd7f9061edc1020a411ebccbb319b47ec\" data-section-id=\"WVdPtK0\" data-sememe-id=\"4MW3KN0\">paresis</a>, manifesting as a breathy, weak voice and paramedian <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal fold</a> positioning on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">laryngoscopy</a>. Additionally, it can affect <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-section-id=\"J9csoe0\">swallowing</a> coordination, particularly with liquids. The intact <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Zac08e08784826ab14a9615a73789c357\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Zac08e08784826ab14a9615a73789c357\" data-section-id=\"xAXEN00\" data-sememe-id=\"hNbca8\">gag reflex</a> and normal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-section-id=\"p9cLoe0\">tongue</a> strength localize the injury to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">recurrent laryngeal nerve</a>, which supplies the laryngeal muscles.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point: </b></span>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">recurrent laryngeal nerve</a> can be injured during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Zb456e92a385b8cd5f724158a5119232b\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Zb456e92a385b8cd5f724158a5119232b\" data-section-id=\"PLbWB8\" data-sememe-id=\"rVbfDs\">thyroidectomy</a>, which can lead to <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-section-id=\"LZ1wX20\" data-sememe-id=\"xSaEb4\">aspiration</a> due to its role in innervating the intrinsic muscles of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\">larynx</a> and protecting the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Z5a964768554f93e7967999032fda236f\">airway</a> during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-section-id=\"J9csoe0\">swallowing</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_61e138933ee55.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Zde3eeca9b0a95fa5dd1f78523e5f9f52\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Zde3eeca9b0a95fa5dd1f78523e5f9f52\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"qqaCzl\">glossopharyngeal nerve</a> provides sensory innervation to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=es0xFh&anker=Z968b5390337aed04c970eeafe91772f7\" data-learningcard-id=\"es0xFh\" data-anker=\"Z968b5390337aed04c970eeafe91772f7\" data-section-id=\"McWM140\" data-sememe-id=\"7FY4jI\">oropharynx</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">posterior</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z2ede91c43f398344fca83c88a7d75d15\" data-section-id=\"p9cLoe0\">tongue</a> and motor innervation to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=es0xFh&anker=Zdb98cdda4d8fe5af9745897e4ff654a1\" data-learningcard-id=\"es0xFh\" data-anker=\"Zdb98cdda4d8fe5af9745897e4ff654a1\" data-section-id=\"McWM140\" data-sememe-id=\"6VcjvY0\">stylopharyngeus muscle</a>. Injury would affect the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Zac08e08784826ab14a9615a73789c357\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Zac08e08784826ab14a9615a73789c357\" data-section-id=\"xAXEN00\" data-sememe-id=\"hNbca8\">gag reflex</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z1cfc585a665e281efc5b5180869ace26\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z1cfc585a665e281efc5b5180869ace26\" data-section-id=\"OCcIHe0\">taste</a>, or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-section-id=\"J9csoe0\">swallowing</a> initiation, not cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Zc2f4107b6e40254227fa91ccae0a16aa\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Zc2f4107b6e40254227fa91ccae0a16aa\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"JsXsDz\">dysphonia</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6251da6a569c47455f57936d87b95bf8\" data-section-id=\"LrXw3z\" data-sememe-id=\"-EWDyM0\">vocal fold paralysis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>The external branch of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z3ec0727ed1928536a5394e5d904dfa8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z3ec0727ed1928536a5394e5d904dfa8e\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"HgXK9x\">superior laryngeal nerve</a> innervates the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z550102c2226ff0dfa2e341272e35f11a\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z550102c2226ff0dfa2e341272e35f11a\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"njX7ay\">cricothyroid muscle</a>, affecting pitch modulation. Injury results in subtle voice changes, not significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal fold</a> movement impairment. The breathy voice and paramedian <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal fold</a> position suggest <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">recurrent laryngeal nerve</a> dysfunction.</div>",
