    {
      "text": "A 42-year-old woman presents three days after total thyroidectomy with muscle cramping and perioral numbness. Vital signs are normal. Laboratory studies show serum calcium of 7.1 mg/dL. What is the most likely cause of her presentation?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Postoperative hematoma formation"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Recurrent laryngeal nerve injury"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Residual thyroid tissue hypersecretion"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Surgical site infection"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Inadvertent parathyroid gland removal"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 5,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Postoperative <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z02cbf02e95d7b84aac89b0eb532c01cd\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z02cbf02e95d7b84aac89b0eb532c01cd\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"zCaru5\">hematoma</a> would typically present with neck swelling, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>, and potentially respiratory compromise rather than the biochemical abnormality and neuromuscular symptoms seen in this patient.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">Recurrent laryngeal nerve</a> injury would manifest as voice changes and <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7dZ4r0\">hoarseness</span> rather than <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hg0K92&anker=Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hg0K92\" data-anker=\"Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-sememe-id=\"pqYLzJ\">hypocalcemia</a> and the associated neuromuscular symptoms described.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Residual <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid</a> tissue would not cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hg0K92&anker=Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hg0K92\" data-anker=\"Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-sememe-id=\"pqYLzJ\">hypocalcemia</a>. Any remaining <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid</a> tissue would more likely contribute to hyperthyroid symptoms rather than the <span data-sememe-id=\"YrWnf50\">calcium</span> abnormality presented.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=550ikg&anker=Z52e61f3001c4e85b8f008d4ed8bde7fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"550ikg\" data-anker=\"Z52e61f3001c4e85b8f008d4ed8bde7fd\" data-section-id=\"eOcxrc0\" data-sememe-id=\"goaFYl\">Surgical site infection</a> would typically present with local signs of inflammation, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, and systemic symptoms rather than isolated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hg0K92&anker=Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hg0K92\" data-anker=\"Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-sememe-id=\"pqYLzJ\">hypocalcemia</a> with neuromuscular manifestations.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) CORRECT:</h4>Correct â€“ <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hg0K92&anker=Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hg0K92\" data-anker=\"Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-sememe-id=\"pqYLzJ\">Hypocalcemia</a> following <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Zb456e92a385b8cd5f724158a5119232b\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Zb456e92a385b8cd5f724158a5119232b\" data-section-id=\"PLbWB8\" data-sememe-id=\"rVbfDs\">thyroidectomy</a> results from accidental removal of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Z6dff947cfaf3727d5e6bb595da14a70e\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Z6dff947cfaf3727d5e6bb595da14a70e\" data-section-id=\"88cOoV0\" data-sememe-id=\"MqXM__\">parathyroid glands</a> during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a>. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Z6dff947cfaf3727d5e6bb595da14a70e\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Z6dff947cfaf3727d5e6bb595da14a70e\" data-section-id=\"88cOoV0\" data-sememe-id=\"MqXM__\">parathyroid glands</a> are small and located at the back of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid gland</a> at variable locations, making complete preservation technically challenging. Accidental removal leads to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sg0yu2&anker=Zc6f73f840fa12edb04fdb347942de27d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sg0yu2\" data-anker=\"Zc6f73f840fa12edb04fdb347942de27d\" data-sememe-id=\"VebGBs\">hypoparathyroidism</a> and explains the resulting <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hg0K92&anker=Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hg0K92\" data-anker=\"Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-sememe-id=\"pqYLzJ\">hypocalcemia</a> with associated neuromuscular manifestations.</div>",
