      "text": "A 38-year-old woman undergoes hemithyroidectomy for treatment of localized, well-differentiated papillary thyroid carcinoma. The lesion is removed with clear margins. However, during the surgery, a structure lying directly adjacent to the superior thyroid artery at the upper pole of the thyroid lobe is damaged. This patient is most likely to experience which of the following symptoms?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Voice pitch limitation"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Perioral paresthesias"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Ineffective cough"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Weakness of shoulder shrug"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Difficulty swallowing"
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "text": "Shortness of breath"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Voice pitch limitation</b></span> is caused by damage to the external branch of the <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z3ec0727ed1928536a5394e5d904dfa8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z3ec0727ed1928536a5394e5d904dfa8e\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"HgXK9x\">superior laryngeal nerve</a></b></span> (SLN), which occurs in up to 30% of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid</a> dissections. The external branch of the SLN innervates the <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z550102c2226ff0dfa2e341272e35f11a\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z550102c2226ff0dfa2e341272e35f11a\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"njX7ay\">cricothyroid muscle</a></b></span>, which is responsible for lengthening, thinning, and stiffening the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cords</a> and increases the pitch of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z9db3c5c72afcaeacf3e091a865b372ff\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z9db3c5c72afcaeacf3e091a865b372ff\" data-section-id=\"8tcO2V0\">phonation</a>. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z550102c2226ff0dfa2e341272e35f11a\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z550102c2226ff0dfa2e341272e35f11a\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"njX7ay\">cricothyroid muscle</a> is the only tensor of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cord</a>, and its <span data-sememe-id=\"70d4ho0\">denervation</span> results in an inability to increase the pitch of the voice or produce explosive sounds as well as easy voice fatigability.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_689db6782b69b7.90198576.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>The thyroid gland is located in front of the trachea in the lower neck and consists of two lobes connected by an isthmus. A third pyramidal lobe extending from the isthmus is present in 50% of patients. This third lobe is a remnant of the thyroglossal duct.</p><p>The parathyroid glands are located posterior to the thyroid gland; they may vary in number and location. The recurrent laryngeal nerves (RLN) branch off from the vagus nerve; the left RLN loops under the aortic arch, and the right RLN passes beneath the subclavian artery. Both RLNs are vulnerable to injury during thyroid surgery as they ascend to the larynx behind the thyroid gland. Unilateral RLN injury may result in hoarseness, and bilateral RLN injury may cause dyspnea and stridor.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Perioral <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Z945b9f13c684a6d5efb4e12182a7acf0\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Z945b9f13c684a6d5efb4e12182a7acf0\" data-section-id=\"FAXgl00\" data-sememe-id=\"lkbvLF\">paresthesia</a></span> after <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\">thyroid surgery</a> is a result of <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hg0K92&anker=Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hg0K92\" data-anker=\"Z50c20097f106413aab2d2eb1b550c96d\" data-sememe-id=\"pqYLzJ\">hypocalcemia</a></span> secondary to <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sg0yu2&anker=Zc6f73f840fa12edb04fdb347942de27d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sg0yu2\" data-anker=\"Zc6f73f840fa12edb04fdb347942de27d\" data-sememe-id=\"VebGBs\">hypoparathyroidism</a></span>, usually due to unintentional removal of one or several of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Z6dff947cfaf3727d5e6bb595da14a70e\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Z6dff947cfaf3727d5e6bb595da14a70e\" data-section-id=\"88cOoV0\" data-sememe-id=\"MqXM__\">parathyroid glands</a>. <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sg0yu2&anker=Zc6f73f840fa12edb04fdb347942de27d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sg0yu2\" data-anker=\"Zc6f73f840fa12edb04fdb347942de27d\" data-sememe-id=\"VebGBs\">Hypoparathyroidism</a></span> is the most frequent complication of total or near-total <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Zb456e92a385b8cd5f724158a5119232b\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Zb456e92a385b8cd5f724158a5119232b\" data-section-id=\"PLbWB8\" data-sememe-id=\"rVbfDs\">thyroidectomy</a>. However, the superior <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Z6dff947cfaf3727d5e6bb595da14a70e\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Z6dff947cfaf3727d5e6bb595da14a70e\" data-section-id=\"88cOoV0\" data-sememe-id=\"MqXM__\">parathyroid glands</a> are most commonly found inferior to the superior <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Zf67f8be5d8e2b577ccc34575c1940df8\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Zf67f8be5d8e2b577ccc34575c1940df8\" data-section-id=\"WJcPGW0\">artery</a> and the external branch of the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">recurrent laryngeal nerve</a></span> and are thus less likely to be injured in this patient.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Ineffective <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a> could result from unilateral <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">recurrent laryngeal nerve</a></span> (RLN) injury. This causes the affected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal fold</a> to rest in the paramedian or lateralized position. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">Coughing</a>, which requires transient tight <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z87ec63567880be15c1a05c11307f3959\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z87ec63567880be15c1a05c11307f3959\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"wi0hFf\">glottic</a> closure, may then become ineffective. While unilateral RLN injury can occur during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\">thyroid surgery</a>, the nerve is unlikely to be damaged during ligation of the superior <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Zf67f8be5d8e2b577ccc34575c1940df8\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Zf67f8be5d8e2b577ccc34575c1940df8\" data-section-id=\"WJcPGW0\">artery</a>. Instead, the RLN is at risk during preparation of the inferior pole of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid gland</a>, as it runs close to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Z5cea93ca86b858848829edf71f1ae7c5\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Z5cea93ca86b858848829edf71f1ae7c5\" data-section-id=\"uFcpPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"-hcDgX0\">inferior thyroid artery</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3u0SI3&anker=Z7d581b4f2422609e12fc9ec6ba4e6a91\" data-learningcard-id=\"3u0SI3\" data-anker=\"Z7d581b4f2422609e12fc9ec6ba4e6a91\" data-section-id=\"WVdPtK0\">Weakness</a> of shoulder shrug can occur due to <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z9f131c4795a1b65efbeafe135c9b4035\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z9f131c4795a1b65efbeafe135c9b4035\" data-section-id=\"orX0Rz\" data-sememe-id=\"hqacyl\">spinal accessory nerve injury</a></span> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6e6ba8f8387793dc7660178e8b68beb8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6e6ba8f8387793dc7660178e8b68beb8\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"HqaK-l\">cranial nerve XI</a>). The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6e6ba8f8387793dc7660178e8b68beb8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6e6ba8f8387793dc7660178e8b68beb8\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"HqaK-l\">spinal accessory nerve</a> runs through the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=b60HjS&anker=Z1232f3b1e3f2a9a97e5cb1d4b1310ba6\" data-learningcard-id=\"b60HjS\" data-anker=\"Z1232f3b1e3f2a9a97e5cb1d4b1310ba6\" data-section-id=\"9CcN8e0\" data-sememe-id=\"GfbBnG\">posterior triangle of the neck</a></span> and supplies the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=w60hMS&anker=Z7803b20e24ad3c01b765f982bc81b365\" data-learningcard-id=\"w60hMS\" data-anker=\"Z7803b20e24ad3c01b765f982bc81b365\" data-section-id=\"yucdFV0\" data-sememe-id=\"hcXcXC\">trapezius muscle</a>, which is responsible for shoulder shrugging. However, injury to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z6e6ba8f8387793dc7660178e8b68beb8\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z6e6ba8f8387793dc7660178e8b68beb8\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"HqaK-l\">spinal accessory nerve</a> would not be expected during a <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Zcad0871d6e9619fa1f5437cbc53910ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Zcad0871d6e9619fa1f5437cbc53910ba\" data-section-id=\"PLbWB8\" data-sememe-id=\"Ln0wFg\">hemithyroidectomy</a></span>. The most common causes of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z9f131c4795a1b65efbeafe135c9b4035\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z9f131c4795a1b65efbeafe135c9b4035\" data-section-id=\"orX0Rz\" data-sememe-id=\"hqacyl\">spinal accessory nerve injury</a> include <span data-sememe-id=\"sebtZG\">biopsy</span> of the cervical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=960NMS&anker=Z5fb5bd23c6255d2e24514ab1610448ae\" data-learningcard-id=\"960NMS\" data-anker=\"Z5fb5bd23c6255d2e24514ab1610448ae\" data-section-id=\"ZEcZ8V0\" data-sememe-id=\"yhXdgB\">lymph nodes</a> in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">posterior</a> triangle and radical <span data-sememe-id=\"wrchjd0\">neck dissection</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Difficulty <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-section-id=\"J9csoe0\">swallowing</a> and increased risk of <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-section-id=\"LZ1wX20\" data-sememe-id=\"xSaEb4\">aspiration</a></span> can occur in bilateral injury to the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">recurrent laryngeal nerve</a></span> (RLN), which innervates all the intrinsic muscles of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\">larynx</a> except the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z550102c2226ff0dfa2e341272e35f11a\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z550102c2226ff0dfa2e341272e35f11a\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"njX7ay\">cricothyroid muscle</a></span>. It also carries sensory input from the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\">larynx</a> below the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cords</a>. The RLN can be injured during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\">thyroid surgery</a> because it passes close to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Z5cea93ca86b858848829edf71f1ae7c5\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Z5cea93ca86b858848829edf71f1ae7c5\" data-section-id=\"uFcpPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"-hcDgX0\">inferior thyroid artery</a> on its ascent to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\">larynx</a>. Unilateral damage to the external branch of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z3ec0727ed1928536a5394e5d904dfa8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z3ec0727ed1928536a5394e5d904dfa8e\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"HgXK9x\">superior laryngeal nerve</a> is unlikely to cause difficulty <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Zce4517a7972cca14ab569ee1f09809ba\" data-section-id=\"J9csoe0\">swallowing</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_61e138933ee55.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>F) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">Shortness of breath</a> may be caused by bilateral injury to the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zebd54cbf80398d72905d2b786bd397e6\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"FgXgCx\">recurrent laryngeal nerve</a></span> (RLN), which can be injured during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wl0h_T&anker=Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\" data-learningcard-id=\"wl0h_T\" data-anker=\"Z21eeb82b6c053cc0ed27a0cb781354fa\">thyroid surgery</a> because it passes <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">lateral</a> to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Za09b3ec4cbcf889fc4f7b34cecb45f4d\" data-section-id=\"8FcOPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"c6aaPl\">thyroid gland</a>, adjacent to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=i60JkS&anker=Z5cea93ca86b858848829edf71f1ae7c5\" data-learningcard-id=\"i60JkS\" data-anker=\"Z5cea93ca86b858848829edf71f1ae7c5\" data-section-id=\"uFcpPV0\" data-sememe-id=\"-hcDgX0\">inferior thyroid artery</a>, on its ascent to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\">larynx</a>. The RLN innervates the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z2a8661f5d86e84fe04d55aa9a53a2884\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z2a8661f5d86e84fe04d55aa9a53a2884\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"MjXMay\">posterior cricoarytenoids</a></span>, which are responsible for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cord</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Ze7ee84a752136265c266f18b52599a02\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Ze7ee84a752136265c266f18b52599a02\" data-section-id=\"M6cMlW0\" data-sememe-id=\"dTcopb0\">abduction</a>. In cases of bilateral RLN injury, the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z43190ee70947fd8eeb42db18835a7366\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ajXQ_B\">vocal cords</a> are unable to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Ze7ee84a752136265c266f18b52599a02\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Ze7ee84a752136265c266f18b52599a02\" data-section-id=\"M6cMlW0\" data-sememe-id=\"dTcopb0\">abduct</a>, which restricts air entry into the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Zf4e46fc2988b6146686e641dedf19964\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Zf4e46fc2988b6146686e641dedf19964\" data-section-id=\"Nvc-Ze0\">trachea</a> and can lead to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">shortness of breath</a>. Unilateral damage to the external branch of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Z3ec0727ed1928536a5394e5d904dfa8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Z3ec0727ed1928536a5394e5d904dfa8e\" data-section-id=\"Ftcg2V0\" data-sememe-id=\"HgXK9x\">superior laryngeal nerve</a> is unlikely to cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">shortness of breath</a>.</div>",
      "hint": "The external branch of the superior laryngeal nerve lies directly adjacent to the superior thyroid artery at the upper pole of the thyroid lobe. If the artery is ligated during surgery, it may be damaged.",
